&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Occupational Therapist (Adult Mental Health)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;32 hours per week over 5 days&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;12 month Fixed Term Contract (maternity cover)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a skilled, motivated and passionate Occupational Therapist (OT) to join the Therapies Team at the Stonebow Unit.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Stonebow Unit is a mental health in-patient facility for working age adults and older adults with functional and organic conditions.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;You will work as part of a dedicated in-patient multi-disciplinary team under the supervision of senior Occupational Therapists to provide occupational therapy assessment and treatment for a designated caseload across the inpatient wards.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Occupational Therapy service across Worcestershire Health and Care NHS Trust utilises the Model of Human Occupation as the first informing evidence base, using standardised assessment tools and evidence based intervention plans. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;You will have a passion for working in mental health services, excellent communication and interaction skills and motivation to further develop your practice as an Occupational Therapist.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Patients will be supported to access their local community from hospital as part of discharge preparation and a valid UK driving licence is essential.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The successful candidate will be supported to develop their knowledge and skills in using the Model of Human Occupation,. Regular supervision, reflective practise and training opportunities will be actively encouraged. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;For further details or to arrange an informal visit contact &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span&gt;Gail Mathews, Occupational Therapy Manager, Stonebow Unit &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span&gt;gail.mathews@nhs.net&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt; or 01432 364048&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Closing date: 6/11/2020 Interview date: 20/11/2020&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
